---
/**
 * Why this matters — three positions, written as prose, not stabbed.
 */
import '../styles/why.css';
---
<section class="why" id="how">
  <div class="why-inner">
    <div class="why-stat">
      <p class="why-stat__k">A consultant in the budget process, not a consultant&rsquo;s invoice.</p>
      <p class="why-stat__v">Run an impact study yourself, on your own data, when the question gets asked, instead of waiting three weeks for an outside firm to finish theirs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-stat">
      <p class="why-stat__k">Built on data your team already has.</p>
      <p class="why-stat__v">Administrative records, payroll detail, and high-frequency public sources, not national averages from a 2017 input-output table.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-stat">
      <p class="why-stat__k">Numbers a reviewer can verify.</p>
      <p class="why-stat__v">Every assumption, source, and method ships with the run, so a council member or grant reviewer can check the work without opening the spreadsheet.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
